<bug>
    <id>8260</id>
    <title>Admin.setAppProperties will not set child Applications Settings</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Today_ we noticed that when we entered permissions mode (api_client-&gt;begin_permissions_mode) for our new created child applications_ we could not set the properties (api_client-&gt;admin_setAppProperties)_ not even simple ones like change title or callback_url.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">It returns the error  Application does not have permission for this action</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">FACT: Our code that preforms this action was working earlier in the week and has not changed_ so something must have changed with the Facebook API.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">This is a problem for us because our business is based around creating apps for people_ so it is a big deal.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
